Question;Answer
What provided hope, education, and medicine during the Medieval Ages?;The Roman Catholic Church
What ended the European practice of human sacrifice and polygamy?;The Roman Catholic Church
What can different levels of power be called?;Hierarchy
What abuses occurred in the Church from 800s – 1000s?;a)Bribery b)Having children
What movement cleaned up the Church?;The Cluniac Reforms
What was it called when someone spoke against a belief of the church?;Heresy
What was a punishment for heresy?;Excommunication – a person would be kicked out of the church
What did cardinals do?;Cardinals advised the pope, and they chose the pope
